---
description: Always use z.strictObject() instead of z.object() with Zod
globs: ["**/*.ts", "**/*.tsx"]
alwaysApply: true
---
# Zod: prefer `z.strictObject` over `z.object`

Always use `z.strictObject()` — it rejects unknown keys at parse time, preventing
silent data leaks and schema drift. `z.object()` is forbidden and will fail the
ESLint `no-restricted-syntax` rule.

```ts
// ✅ correct
const Foo = z.strictObject({ id: z.string() });

// ❌ forbidden — ESLint error
const Foo = z.object({ id: z.string() });
```

**Exception:** `env.ts` files may use `z.object()` — env schemas validate
`process.env` and unknown-key rejection adds no value there. The ESLint rule
is disabled for `**/env.ts` via an override in `eslint.config.ts`.
